This project was about developing software using Waterfall software development methodologies, in order to control a Finch Robot, which is a easily programmable robot. It will be connected to a battery and a raspberry PI to create self-contained mobile unit to control the robot remotely, as a result Finch will be able to partake in a game of football.

Hardware and software used
Hardware used
Finch Robot,
Raspberry PI,
Battery,
Wifi adapter,
And Memory card
Camera 
Software used
Putty
Eclipse
Smart Git

Features of the software
Language used: Java
Xming Server: used to export UI from PI to Computer
Capture image using Raspberry PI camera module
Transforming colour image into greyscale image
Applying Otsu Filter to separate foreground and background of the image
Using Binary image to locate football


